OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1780661501
OL,3,CCouncil officers wanted to sack
OL,4,Cstriking bin workers, says ex-
OL,5,CBirmingham leader
OL,7,FBirmingham's former council leader has
OL,8,Fclaimed unelected officers were
OL,9,F"pushing to dismiss" bin workers
OL,10,Fduring the long-running strike.
OL,12,FIn his first intervention after losing
OL,13,Fhis seat, John Cotton hit back after
OL,14,FBirmingham City Council said there was
OL,15,F"no deal" to end the industrial action.
OL,17,FThe bin strike has now dragged on for
OL,18,F17 months, causing major disruption to
OL,19,Fwaste collections across the city.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@TO]wD@AOUwD@IO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/17
