PN,37104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1780661501
OL,3,CCouncil officers wanted to sack
OL,4,Cstriking bin workers, says ex-
OL,5,CBirmingham leader
OL,7,F"The terms of the proposed deal were
OL,8,Ffair to the workforce and to the
OL,9,Ftaxpayer: ending a year-long strike,
OL,10,Fwhilst avoiding creating structural
OL,11,Fequal pay liabilities of the kind that
OL,12,Fhave caused so much damage to
OL,13,FBirmingham over the last fifteen
OL,14,Fyears."
OL,16,FSpeaking to ITV News Central, West
OL,17,FMidlands Mayor recently accused
OL,18,FBirmingham City Council officials of
OL,19,Fhampering bin strike deal.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@GO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/17
