SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1780661501
OL,3,CCouncil officers wanted to sack
OL,4,Cstriking bin workers, says ex-
OL,5,CBirmingham leader
OL,7,FHe pledged at the time that "a re-
OL,8,Felected Labour administration under my
OL,9,Fleadership" would prioritise signing
OL,10,Foff the deal after polling day.
OL,12,FBut Labour lost control of the council
OL,13,Fin the elections, leaving no party
OL,14,Fwith enough seats to govern outright.
OL,16,FUnite later warned the proposed
OL,17,Fagreement now "hangs in the balance",
OL,18,Fclaiming officers and government-
OL,19,Fappointed commissioners were
OL,20,F"potentially ready to pull the plug".
OL,26,@oD@]OUqD@KO]yD@OOUyD@dO]|D@AOU|D@dO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G11/17
