PN,37115
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1780661501
OL,3,CCouncil officers wanted to sack
OL,4,Cstriking bin workers, says ex-
OL,5,CBirmingham leader
OL,7,FUnite the Union has weighed in to side
OL,8,Fwith the former leader John Cotton,
OL,9,Fwith its general secretary Sharon
OL,10,FGraham saying, "As Lord Barber and
OL,11,FMayor Parker have both said, the deal
OL,12,Fto end this dispute has been
OL,13,Fnegotiated and agreed.
OL,15,F"The continued attempts by unelected
OL,16,Fcouncil officers and commissioners to
OL,17,Fblock, delay and throw into doubt this
OL,18,Fdeal is unacceptable and will simply
OL,19,Fnot work.
OL,26,@rD@POUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G15/17
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37116
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1780661501
OL,3,CCouncil officers wanted to sack
OL,4,Cstriking bin workers, says ex-
OL,5,CBirmingham leader
OL,7,F"We look forward to the elected
OL,8,Fmembers of the council agreeing the
OL,9,Fprocess for the implementation of the
OL,10,Fdeal, so the usual ballot of members
OL,11,Fcan take place.
OL,13,F"Workers and residents have put up
OL,14,Fwith enough of the constant dither and
OL,15,Fdelay. This is a good deal for workers
OL,16,Fand residents and it needs to be
OL,17,Fswiftly finalised."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUyD@SO]
